<body>

    <% include ./partials/navbar %>

    <section class="hero is-dark">
        <div class="hero-body">
            <div class="container is-fluid">
                <h1 class="title">
                    List's Privacy Policy
                </h1>
                <h2 class="subtitle">
                    Information on how List collects your data
                </h2>

            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="container is-fluid">

        <section class="section">
            <h2 class="title">Data Collection</h2>
            <p class="subtitle">By using this service, List needs to collect some data for it to work.
                The data collected are
                your:
            </p>

            <ol>
                <li>Spotify's username and display name (It's not your email)</li>
                <li>Spotify's user id (A random identifier string which is tied to your Spotify account)</li>
                <li>Spotify's liked songs (Latest 50)</li>
                <li>Spotify's profile picture(s)</li>
                <li>Spotify's recently played songs (Latest 50)</li>
            </ol>

        </section>


        <section class="section">
            <h2 class="title">How does List process my data?</h2>
            <p>When you use our service, List automatically creates a user profile based on your
                name, id and liked
                songs! The name is used to display when you visit the user page while the id is used so that there is no
                duplicates of spotify accounts on the server and the liked songs is used to display to the public.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <h2 class="title">A new type of data is collected! When is the Privacy Policy effective?</h2>
            <p>When a new data is collected and you are an existing user, The new Privacy Policy is effective only when you Sign In again. But as for new users, at that point of time of Signing Up, the privacy policy is effective already.</p>
        </section>
    </div>

